@tmt [τ, τ] the new scoring system will have a smooth transition function from the current reward landscape to winner takes all. We will be releasing the code fairly soon, but it will then become increasingly winner-takes-all over time, so no worries about adapting!

Regarding the 1000 miner question: Initially we won't be needing 1k miners, but we are balancing innovation (winner-takes-all tasks) with throughput (inference task). As people begin to adopt SN1, we will see inference be used more and more. 

One idea for instance is that once someone develops a high quality code completion model, we may take that model into our inference model zoo and offer it as a vscode plugin. That's still a good way away, but shows how this can be productised. If any of the products get enough traction, we likely need a large amount of miners running inference:)

